Eight poets and musicians will be performing in Newlands on Saturday. CAPE TOWN - Poets from across Cape Town will lend their voices to a cause which aims to help girls in need of sanitary pads. Slam for Blood is an initiative which aims to raise awareness around the issue of a lack of hygiene products that thousands of girls and women face daily.Eight poets and musicians will be performing in Newlands on Saturday.Anyone wishing to attend can gain entry with a pack of pads.Poet and organiser Roch Kester say: It s a brainchild of Chani Macauley and this is one of the aspects that she s been doing with regards to menstruation dignity. We ve been working in Hanover Park, but we re trying to create a movement and hopefully we ll be able to reach beyond that as well. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)